<hl>
<seg id=1> Information Minister Mohamed Rahmat: "The Burning of Indonesia" demonstrators should not become the puppet of external forces. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Kuala Lumpur Malaysian Information Minister Mohamed Rahmat said that"The Burning of Indonesia" demonstrators should not become the puppet of external forces to do damage to the country. On the contrary, they should choose a wiser way to express themselves. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that compared with the ways of violence and stirring up internal strife, it's more effective to choose an intellectual way to express yourselves. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to the Malaysian News Agency, yesterday after the Family Day Activity of the Ministry of Information, Mohamed Rahmat told the media that the government had taken some actions to let the people express themselves. Through the 500 "Speaking-Out Centers" set up in different areas of the country, people could show their opinions to the country in the right way. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said that the government would consider the opinions of the people, and meet the needs of the people. </seg>
<seg id=6> He emphasized that this was the way for a democratic country. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He also advised the demonstrators to consider the results of demonstration because since the independence of Indonesia 41 years ago, it's the people's efforts and contribution that had brought the prosperity today. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that when the external forces against the government supported the demonstrators, they didn't realize that it's a behavior for betraying national dignity. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> He addressed: "If the foreigners want to invest in Malaysia, they are welcome; but if they pay for the demonstrations, we must protest them." </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
